<subSubSection id="54214356855EDE4B93A756E317277DCA" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" type="description">
<paragraph id="26C943EA5BDE0256CE95DFE78273190A" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D0ADAD230DE0721F96CF9B98DA10561" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">
Much-branched undershrub to 30 cm, stem and all vegetative parts grey-sericeous, branches rigid and with few leaves, ascending at about 60°. Leaves sessile, 6-20 
<normalizedToken id="F8F0C9E718F00D754242A1058C2807E2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-5 mm, linear to narrowly oblong, obtuse, entire, narrowed at both ends. Flowers 1-3, arising in the axils of small bracts on a rigid peduncle; bracts 2 
<normalizedToken id="65FFBE3DAD0F06769961CF7B8CCA7A7E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 mm, triangular; peduncles 0.8-2.5 cm; bracteoles c. 1 mm; pedicels 0-1.5 mm, sepals 3-3.5 
<normalizedToken id="6F81B377FB65D844F06F9E65BB0F083B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm, oblong-elliptic, densely sericeous, outer rounded, inner mucronulate; corolla 0.9-1 cm long, white, midpetaline bands sericeous, weakly lobed; ovary globose, pubescent (or glabrous in 
<emphasis id="0589CC2B8C6F9DC6760853E597E486A1" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Rechinger</emphasis>
35336), style glabrous, divided c. 4 mm above base, stigmas 1.5 mm. Capsule and seeds unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
