<emphasis id="E46C1867D06EB1D327719D6560F6483B" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Breckle</emphasis>
4828).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8B8BA028C907068DE7650B5465AC6757" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" type="notes">
<paragraph id="2A17152DAE52F09762191EAB54631306" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="65719CD6A381DBCF9B3973EF460BA77D" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">
This poorly known species is characterised by the grey sericeous stems and leaves, small sericeous mucronulate calyx and short corolla. It may be only a form of 
<taxonomicName id="4A0D0E4C95DCDD0B76CA87CDB7627184" authorityName="Boiss. &amp; Buhse, Nouv. Mem. Soc. Imp. Naturalises Moscou 12: 148. 1860. (Boissier and Buhse" authorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus eremophilus" order="Solanales" pageId="149" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eremophilus">
<emphasis id="7DE3322173C3139E544590A3B7C64386" italics="true" pageId="149" pageNumber="150">Convolvulus eremophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
